		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>specifying MMC3 earlier vs later revisions IRQ differences ?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Are there different iNES mapper numbers that are assigned to the alternate MMC3 behaviors?  I have some code that works fine in Nestopia (irq can be triggered 1 scanline later) which would be the later mmc3 behavior.
<br />
<br />However, on powerpak and nintendulator irqs one scanline later are getting missed, which would be the earlier mmc3 behavior.
<br />
<br />Is there a way I just choose a different iNES mapper to get the later mmc3 behavior, or should I just put in a spacial case in my code to handle the missing IRQ?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Drag</b> [ Sat Mar 31, 2012 12:02 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Right now, there isn't, so which MMC3 irq behavior is emulated is up to the emulator.
<br />
<br />At some point, the newer MMC3 behavior (IRQ fires when the counter is <em>equal</em> to 0, instead of only when it <em>reaches</em> 0) was considered the "normal" behavior, so I'm kinda surprised to see the older behavior being implemented.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


